<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 09 at 5:46AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Pushmataha, western Latimer and Pittsburg Counties through 615 AM
CDT...
At 546 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Savanna, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Alderson...
Haywood...                        Mcalester Regional Airport...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Arpelar...
Gowen...                          Dow...
Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
